<br>
First of all, your specialization points that you get every time you level, there is a set amount of these. At level 50, you will have gotten a certain number of points to use and then you are done after that. So, the reason I got screwed is because I did not know this. I was putting points into each of my magic lines because I didn't know what each line offered, and had no idea I would be screwed from checking them all out. So basically what happened is that I was keeping all my magic specializations (Mana, Light, Void) about even. Because of this, I was ending up about 3 spell levels behind at level 12. I only had access to a level 9 spell in my specialization magic line because since I hadn't focused my points, I wasn't advancing ahead to my level in any spell line. After checking out what each magic line offered, I decided to go with Mana magic (which gives me access to the Vacummancy line of spells - dd/snares, disease). I checked it out, and the only spell I would end up not having is my level 50 snare/dd. I didn't care too much about that, but I realized that I would also always be 3 levels behind or so when it came to new spells. Which would be my end every time in a rvr (realm vs realm) situation.<br>
<br>
Bleh.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I know this was confusing, but just check out this site and you will see what I mean. Click on the Character Builder.<br>
<br>
daoc.catacombs.com<br>
<br>
They really should have explained this better, I think a lot of people are going to be screwed later on and have to restart. It can be very hard to decide what you want to do because you have to think of pvp as well as hunting. For example, let's take a Nightshade (rogue). Do you want to be a dual wielding, poisoning, melee rogue? A backstabbing, poisoning rogue? A best at stealth/backstabber rogue? Etc, etc, etc. You can't have them all, and you have to decide beforehand what you want to be, or you will end up a level 50 Nightshade who has the Stealth skill of a level 30. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/uencan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Encan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(10/17/01 6:48:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DAoC players might want to read this. =) (&lt;-- Xiltin </span><hr size=1> Wow, thnx for the heads up.  Checking through the limited number of posts available I came to the same conclusion about the seer I have (gonna start him over, I also spread his points across everything <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    )<br>
